commit.message: fix directory lookup for django 3 compatibility
PROTOCOL_TLS of ssl module allow python > 3 and >= 3.5.3

Fix to error message that "AttributeError: module object has no attribute PROTOCOL_TLS"

PROTOCOL_TLS of ssl module allow python 3.5 upper

Support TLSv1_3

TLS 1.3 protocol will be available with PROTOCOL_SSLv23 in OpenSSL >= 1.1.1. There is no dedicated PROTOCOL constant for just TLS 1.3.
https://docs.python.org/2/library/ssl.html#ssl.PROTOCOL_TLS
test and add python 3.7, django 2.0, 2.1 and 2.2 in setup

Fix request timeouts in django >= v2.1.4

Changing SecureHTTPServer from extending WSGIServer to extending
ThreadedWSGIServer appears to resolve the request timeout issue in
django >= v2.1.4.

Update README.rst

Add IPv6 support description.
Add a test view in demo. In order to be able to test something

Bump version; push to pypi
